{
  "texts": [
    "There could be heterogeneity.",
    "However Fig. 2 Generalized spillover index: temperature changes.",
    "Notes: The Generalized Directional Spillover heatmap represents the estimated contribution to the forecast error variance of country i from innovations to country j for temperature using Diebold and Yilmaz (2012).",
    "The off-diagonal column sums represent contributions to Others, while the row sums represent contributions from Others; when these are totaled across countries, we get the Spillover Index numerator.",
    "The figure indicates that there are considerable temperature linkages from one country to another in our sample, and that therefore climate is international or global in nature."
  ]
}